Accuracy requirement study:

TP itvl: 52 Mbps => ~35 kpp => ~780 ticks per TP

Using 27 MHz ticks for out_time is actually accurate enough.

For tp_itvl, we need to estimate tp_idx_inc bwt PCRs:
  for 52 Mbps session, and 100 ms PCR interval, we have about 3500 TPs between
  So using 4096 as max tp_itvl would be very very safe.
This means F.12 for tp_itvl.

If we define tp_itvl as F20.12, we have about 2^19 ticks per TP, which is
good to cover as low as 0.1 Mbps session!


